    <partintro>
             <para>The <emphasis><xref linkend="UsingGmat"
    xrefstyle="select:title"/></emphasis> chapter contains high level and
    introductory information on the sytem. If you need information on how to
    install and run the system, would like a tour of the system, want know how
    to configure data files, or how GMAT is organized, start here.</para>

    <para>The <emphasis><xref linkend="UsingGmat"
    xrefstyle="select:title"/></emphasis> section provides general information
    on GMAT and how to use the software.</para>

    <para>The <emphasis><xref linkend="WelcomeToGmat"
    xrefstyle="select:title"/></emphasis> contains a brief project and
    software overview, including project status, licensing, and
    contributors.</para>

    <para>The <emphasis><xref linkend="GettingStarted"
    xrefstyle="select:title"/></emphasis> section describes how to get and
    install GMAT, how to run the provided samples, and where to turn for
    further help.</para>

    <para>The <emphasis><xref linkend="TourOfGmat"
    xrefstyle="select:title"/></emphasis> is an in-depth guide through some of
    the key interface features, including the Resources tree, Mission tree,
    Command Summary, and Script Editor.</para>

    <note>
      <para>We consider the <emphasis><xref linkend="UserInterfaces"
      xrefstyle="select:title"/></emphasis> section to be essential reading,
      as it describes some fundamental aspects of how GMAT works.</para>
    </note>
     </partintro>

